Responsibilities: 

Perform full spectrum of general office administrative duties including office supplies and equipment, facilities repair
 & maintenance, procurement, mail & courier, printing of stationery/business card, office renovation, etc., outdoor duties may be required;
Leading and scheduling a team of staffs such as company drivers, Office Assistant and receptionist to perform daily operation;
Assist in formulation of office administration procedures;
Provide back-up support duties to reception, including answering phone calls & enquiries, greeting & serving visitors;
Participate in all-round and daily HR operations;
Participate in ad-hoc projects as assigned;

 
Requirements: 

Tertiary educated with minimum 5 years’ relevant working experience;
Proficient in general PC applications;
Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese, Mandarin is a plus;
Self-motivated and able to work independently & under pressure;
Good telephone manner, interpersonal and communication skills;
Self-motivated and able to work independently & under pressure;
Immediate availability is preferred.

Duties and Responsibilities:

Provide full spectrum of administrative support to Senior Management;
Work closely with Senior Management to manage and prioritize daily appointments schedule;
Prepare correspondence and minutes for meeting, reports and presentation materials;
Liaise with external and internal parties for the daily operational issues document handling, filing and data processing;
Maintain close collaboration acting as an administrative liaison with all departments and head office in PRC;
Possesses good judgement in recognizing the scope of authority;
Manage multiple tasks simultaneously and follow through on issues on timely manner;

  Requirements:

Bachelor degree holder or above in Business or related disciplines;
5 years' working experience in secretary or office administration field preferred;
Good computer knowledge in MS Word, Excel and Chinese Word Processing;
Able to work independently with less supervision;
Candidate with less experience will be considered as Assistant Manager;
Good command of English and Chinese, fluent in Mandarin is an advantage.

We offer attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits including 5-day week to the right candidate.  Interested parties please send your application letter with resume stating present and
 expected salary to Human Resources Department, Level 19, 28 Hennessy Road, Hong Kong or e-mail to us.
(Please quote the reference of the post on the envelope)
All information received will be kept in strict confidence and only for recruitment.

What Am I Expected to Do?

Formulating and create digital marketing campaign proposals and sales kit to attract new clients;
Establishing new and existing relationships with potential clients and marketers in Hong Kong, Mainland China and South-East Asia to maximize sales revenues;
Develop various digital marketing campaigns for new and existing clients, including social media, creative video, influencer marketing, mobile marketing (e.g. Mobile
 advertisement, WeChat, Weibo, Facebook, Instagram, Blog, Youtube etc); Supporting managers and directors in participating in briefings, prepare business proposals, pitching and presentations;
Follow up campaign progress and handle clients’ enquiries;
Stay updated with hot topics, popular culture, latest marketing trends and competitors’ activities for collaboration opportunities.

What Background Would Make Me Successful in This Role?

Bachelor degree in Advertising, Communication, Marketing or related disciplines;
0-2 year of digital advertising / digital marketing working experience, especially in Search Engine Marketing (SEM), Social Media, Mobile, eCommence or other digital related
 roles; Fresh Graduate also welcome;
Exposure in digital marketing industry is an advantage;
A natural user of social media such as WeChat, WeiBo, Facebook, Instagram etc.;
Good at Power-point, Excel & Word and strong communication and coordination skills;
Fluency in both written and spoken English and Chinese (including Mandarin). 

 
Benefits We Offer:

5 days’ work + Bank Holidays
15 days annual leave
Medical Coverage
Performance Bonus

All application will be treated in strict confidence. The information provided will be used for selection purpose only. All information of unsuccessful applicants will be destroyed within 12
 months.

