Responsibilities:

Directly reporting to the Department Head, prepare and review facility letter, security documentation, ISDA Master Agreement, loan documents, and instruction letters to solicitors for
 corporate and FI loan applications and complex cases; Assess to justify deviation on documentation/ lending conditions and recommend for further approval;
Check completion and correctness of the conditions precedent and follow-up the conditions subsequent;
Collaboration with external counsel and other stakeholders to close the deal within the timeframe;
Perform other ad hoc projects or assignments


Requirements:

University degree in Business Administration, Finance or related disciplines; Degree holder in Law would be advantage;
Minimum 12 years’ experience in loan documentation, in which 8 years in the role of reviewing and drafting documentation on bilateral, syndication loans, project financing and ISDA;
In-depth and comprehensive understanding the key provisions of APLMA template;
Good knowledge and concept in different corporate banking products (such as vessel, aircraft, acquisition and privatization financing), complex structural transaction as well as cross-border
 financing; Depth of understanding of operation and documentation risks in financial derivative products;
Sound knowledge in banking practice, legal aspects and regulatory requirements of the HKMA and competent authorities of Mainland China;
Capable of identify and resolve the problems independently;
Well-versed in both spoken and written English and Chinese, including Putonghua;
Conversant with MS Office applications and Chinese Word Processing.


We offer competitive remuneration package and promising career opportunities to the successful candidates. Interested parties, please send full
 resume with current & expected salary and the date of availability to The HR Division, G.P.O. Box 2535, HK , or by clicking Apply Now. Please quote reference on your application. Information provided will be treated in strict confidence and
